OL,3,CFate of 'hidden' Stone of Destiny
OL,4,Cfragments traced by researcher
OL,6,FThe Stirling University academic has
OL,7,Fbeen carrying out painstaking research
OL,8,Fto uncover the stories behind several
OL,9,Ffragments which were separated from
OL,10,Fthe original piece when it was
OL,11,Frepaired in secret in 1951.
OL,13,FThe 152kg block was spirited away from
OL,14,FWestminster Abbey by a group of
OL,15,FScottish nationalist students the
OL,16,Fprevious year.
OL,18,FIt broke in two during the audacious
OL,19,Fraid and was repaired by stonemason
OL,20,Fand sympathiser Bertie Gray before
OL,21,Fbeing returned to the police.
