OL,4,Cfragments traced by researcher
OL,6,F"When Scottish nationalists manhandled
OL,7,Fit out of the Coronation Chair and
OL,8,Fsecreted it away from London's
OL,9,FWestminster Abbey on Christmas morning
OL,10,F1950, this caused the English`Scottish
OL,11,Fborder to be closed for the first time
OL,12,Fin 400 years, because, since the 14th
OL,13,Fcentury, nearly all English, later
OL,14,FBritish monarchs, sat over the Stone
OL,15,Fduring their coronation, in an act
OL,16,Fthat symbolised the subjugation of the
OL,17,FScots."
