OL,4,Cfragments traced by researcher
OL,6,FThe stone, also known as the Stone of
OL,7,FScone, currently sits as the
OL,8,Fcentrepiece exhibition of Perth
OL,9,FMuseum, which narrates its centuries-
OL,10,Flong history with the Scottish and
OL,11,Flater British royal families.
OL,13,FThe existence of fragments from the
OL,14,FStone of Destiny has already been
OL,15,Facknowledged ` an inch-sized piece was
OL,16,Fgifted to Mr Salmond by Sir Neil
OL,17,FMacCormick and was kept at SNP
OL,18,Fheadquarters ` but it was only Prof
OL,19,FFoster's research which revealed there
OL,20,Fwere more than 30 in existence.
