OL,4,Cfragments traced by researcher
OL,6,F"Families cared for them, emotionally
OL,7,Fand physically, and we can also trace
OL,8,Fthe progression of fragments to valued
OL,9,Fheirlooms."
OL,11,FWhen Charles was coronated in 2023 the
OL,12,FStone of Destiny was taken to London
OL,13,Fwhere it was mounted in the Coronation
OL,14,FChair, continuing its ancient role in
OL,15,Fthe monarchy.
OL,17,FIt moved to Perth Museum last year,
OL,18,Fhaving previously been kept at
OL,19,FEdinburgh Castle.
