OL,4,Cfragments traced by researcher
OL,6,FDescribing the mysterious Roman
OL,7,Fnumerals on the stone, Prof Foster
OL,8,Fsaid: "I believe Gray, having gathered
OL,9,Fthe 34 fragments, applied the XXXV as
OL,10,Fpart of his finishing touches to the
OL,11,FStone's repair ` the fragments plus
OL,12,Fthe Stone equals 35.
OL,14,F"He used Roman numerals because these
OL,15,Fare easier to scratch into stone and,
OL,16,Fas a mason, he would have been
OL,17,Ffamiliar with historic masons' marks.
